  "prompt": "What are the top 10 inspirational movies of the 21st century?",
  "response": "While the list of top inspirational movies can be subjective and vary based on personal preferences, here are ten widely acclaimed inspirational movies from the 21st century:\n\n1. **The Pursuit of Happyness (2006)** - Starring Will Smith, this film is based on the true story of Chris Gardner\u2019s struggle with homelessness while raising his young son and his determination to achieve success.\n\n2. **Slumdog Millionaire (2008)** - Directed by Danny Boyle, this rags-to-riches story follows a young man from the slums of Mumbai who competes on a game show to win a fortune.\n\n3. **The Blind Side (2009)** - This biographical sports drama stars Sandra Bullock and tells the story of Michael Oher, a homeless teenager who becomes an All-American football player with the help of a caring woman and her family.\n\n4. **The King's Speech (2010)** - This historical drama stars Colin Firth as King George VI, who works to overcome his stammer with the help of a speech therapist.\n\n5. **127 Hours (2010)** - Directed by Danny Boyle, this film is based on the true story of Aron Ralston, a hiker who becomes trapped by a boulder and must make a harrowing decision to survive.\n\n6. **Life of Pi (2012)** - Directed by Ang Lee, this visually stunning film follows a young man who survives a shipwreck and shares a lifeboat with a Bengal tiger.\n\n7. **Whiplash (2014)** - This intense drama stars Miles Teller as a young drummer who strives for greatness under the tutelage of a demanding music teacher played by J.K. Simmons.\n\n8. **Selma (2014)** - Directed by Ava DuVernay, this film chronicles the 1965 Selma to Montgomery voting rights marches led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.\n\n9. **Hidden Figures (2016)** - This film tells the true story of three African-American women at NASA who were instrumental in the success of the early space missions.\n\n10. **A Beautiful Day in the Neighborhood (2019)** - Starring Tom Hanks as Mister Rogers, this film depicts the real-life friendship between Fred Rogers and a journalist, highlighting themes of kindness and understanding.\n\nThese movies have been praised for their powerful storytelling, inspiring characters, and ability to motivate and uplift audiences.",
